Sure, here are some examples of sentences in Serbian that use the word "oku" in different forms and positions:

1. *Oko* mi je jako crveno. (My *eye* is very red.)
2. Vidim *oko* na dnu jezera. (I see a *circle* at the bottom of the lake.)
3. On je *okovan* svojim strahovima. (He is *shackled* by his fears.)
4. *Okrenuo* je glavu na drugu stranu. (He *turned* his head to the other side.)
5. *Okrugli* sto je veoma praktičan. (The *round* table is very practical.)
6. *Oko* kocke ima šest strana. (A *cube* has six sides.)
7. *Oko* nas su visoke planine. (There are high mountains *around* us.)
8. *Okupio* je svoje prijatelje na rođendanu. (He *gathered* his friends for his birthday.)
9. *Oko* naselja su voćnjaci. (There are orchards *near* the settlement.)
10. Ona je *okrenuta* ka budućnosti. (She is *oriented* towards the future.)

Note: I put an asterisk (*) before the word "oku" in each sentence to highlight it. The translations of each sentence are in parentheses.